#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:0.5
msgid 34. Kāṇamātusikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on Kāṇamātu"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.0a
msgid "
msgstr Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.79, pts-cs-bu-pc34.1.1, pts-vp-en.2.321, ms2V_743
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.1
msgid Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.2
msgid Tena kho pana samayena kāṇamātā upāsikā saddhā hoti pasannā."
msgstr "At that  time there was a female lay follower Kāṇamātā who had faith and confidence."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.3
msgid Kāṇā gāmake aññatarassa purisassa dinnā hoti."
msgstr "She had a daughter, Kāṇā, who had been given in marriage to a man in a certain village."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.4
msgid Atha kho kāṇā mātugharaṃ agamāsi kenacideva karaṇīyena."
msgstr "On one occasion Kāṇā went to her mother’s house on some business."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.5
msgid Atha kho kāṇāya sāmiko kāṇāya santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "Kāṇā’s husband sent her a message:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.6
msgid “āgacchatu kāṇā, icchāmi kāṇāya āgatan”ti."
msgstr "“Please come Kāṇā; I want you back.”"

#. VAR: pūvaṃ → pūpaṃ (ṇvādi­mog­gallāne)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.7
msgid Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā “kismiṃ viya rittahatthaṃ gantun”ti pūvaṃ paci."
msgstr "Kāṇamātā thought, “It’s shameful to go empty-handed,” and she baked biscuits."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.8
msgid Pakke pūve aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu kāṇamātāya upāsikāya nivesanaṃ pāvisi."
msgstr "Just when the biscuits were finished, a monk who was an alms-collector entered Kāṇamātā’s house,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.9
msgid Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā tassa bhikkhuno pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr "and she gave him biscuits."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.10
msgid So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi."
msgstr "After leaving, he told another monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.11
msgid Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr "and he too was given biscuits."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.12
msgid So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi. Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr "And the same happened a third time."

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.322
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.13
msgid Yathāpaṭiyattaṃ pūvaṃ parikkhayaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr "At that, all the biscuits were gone."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_744, ms2V_745
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.14
msgid Dutiyampi kho kāṇāya sāmiko kāṇāya santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "A second time Kāṇā’s husband sent her the same message, and everything unfolded as before."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.15
msgid “āgacchatu kāṇā, icchāmi kāṇāya āgatan”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.16
msgid Dutiyampi kho kāṇamātā upāsikā “kismiṃ viya rittahatthaṃ gantun”ti pūvaṃ paci."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.17
msgid Pakke pūve aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu kāṇamātāya upāsikāya nivesanaṃ pāvisi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.18
msgid Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā tassa bhikkhuno pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.19
msgid So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.20
msgid Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.21
msgid So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.22
msgid Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.23
msgid Yathāpaṭiyattaṃ pūvaṃ parikkhayaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.24
msgid Tatiyampi kho kāṇāya sāmiko kāṇāya santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "A third time he sent the same message,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.25
msgid “āgacchatu kāṇā, icchāmi kāṇāya āgataṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.26
msgid Sace kāṇā nāgacchissati, ahaṃ aññaṃ pajāpatiṃ ānessāmī”ti."
msgstr "adding, “If Kāṇā doesn’t come, I’ll find another wife.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.27
msgid Tatiyampi kho kāṇamātā upāsikā kismiṃ viya rittahatthaṃ gantunti pūvaṃ paci."
msgstr "But once again all the biscuits were given to monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.28
msgid Pakke pūve aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu kāṇamātāya upāsikāya nivesanaṃ pāvisi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.29
msgid Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā tassa bhikkhuno pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.30
msgid So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.31
msgid Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.32
msgid So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.33
msgid Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.34
msgid Yathāpaṭiyattaṃ pūvaṃ parikkhayaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.35
msgid Atha kho kāṇāya sāmiko aññaṃ pajāpatiṃ ānesi."
msgstr "Kāṇā’s husband found another wife,"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_746
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.36
msgid Assosi kho kāṇā—“tena kira purisena aññā pajāpati ānītā”ti."
msgstr "and when Kāṇā heard what had happened,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.37
msgid Sā rodantī aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "she cried."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.38
msgid Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena kāṇamātāya upāsikāya nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Soon afterwards, after robing up in the morning, the Master, took his bowl and robe, and went to Kāṇamātā’s house,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.39
msgid upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat down on a prepared seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.40
msgid Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Kāṇamātā approached the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.41
msgid upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.42
msgid Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho kāṇamātaraṃ upāsikaṃ bhagavā etadavoca—“kissāyaṃ kāṇā rodatī”ti?"
msgstr "The Master asked her why Kāṇā was crying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.43
msgid Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "and she told him what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.1.44
msgid Atha kho bhagavā kāṇamātaraṃ upāsikaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi."
msgstr "After instructing, inspiring, and gladdening her with a teaching, the Master rose from his seat and departed."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-pli4.80, pts-cs-bu-pc34.1.2, ms2V_747
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.1
msgid Tena kho pana samayena aññataro sattho rājagahā paṭiyālokaṃ gantukāmo hoti."
msgstr "Around the same time a certain caravan was ready to go south from Rājagaha."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.2
msgid Aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu taṃ satthaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr "A monk who was an alms-collector approached that caravan to get almsfood,"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.323
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.3
msgid Aññataro upāsako tassa bhikkhuno sattuṃ dāpesi."
msgstr "and a lay follower gave him barley-meal."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.4
msgid So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi."
msgstr "After leaving, that monk told another monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.5
msgid Tassapi sattuṃ dāpesi."
msgstr "and he too was given barley-meal."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.6
msgid So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi. Tassapi sattuṃ dāpesi."
msgstr "And the same happened a third time."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.7
msgid Yathāpaṭiyattaṃ pātheyyaṃ parikkhayaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr "At that, all the barley-meal was gone."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.8
msgid Atha kho so upāsako te manusse etadavoca—"
msgstr "That lay follower said to the other people in the caravan,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.9
msgid “ajjaṇho, ayyā, āgametha, yathāpaṭiyattaṃ pātheyyaṃ ayyānaṃ dinnaṃ."
msgstr "“Sirs, please wait one day. I have given my provisions to the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.10
msgid Pātheyyaṃ paṭiyādessāmī”ti."
msgstr "and I need to prepare more provisions.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Nāyyo → nāyya (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.11
msgid “Nāyyo sakkā āgametuṃ, payāto sattho”ti agamaṃsu."
msgstr "“We can’t wait; the caravan is going already.” And they departed."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.12
msgid Atha kho tassa upāsakassa pātheyyaṃ paṭiyādetvā pacchā gacchantassa corā acchindiṃsu."
msgstr "After preparing provisions, that lay follower followed after the caravan, but he was robbed by thieves."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.13
msgid Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.14
msgid “kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā na mattaṃ jānitvā paṭiggahessanti."
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics receive without moderation?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.15
msgid Ayaṃ imesaṃ datvā pacchā gacchanto corehi acchinno”ti."
msgstr "This man gave to them, and then because he was following after the caravan he was robbed by thieves.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_748
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.16
msgid Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.17
msgid Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "and they told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.18
msgid Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.19
msgid “tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmi dasa atthavase paṭicca—"
msgstr "“Well then, monks, I will lay down a training rule for the following ten reasons:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.20
msgid saṃghasuṭṭhutāya, saṃghaphāsutāya … pe … vinayānuggahāya."
msgstr "for the well-being of the Order, for the comfort of the Order, for the restraint of bad people, for the ease of well-behaved monks, for the restraint of corruptions in the present life, for avoiding corruptions in future lives, to give rise to confidence in those without it, to increase the confidence of those who have it, for the continuation of the true Teaching, and for supporting the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.21
msgid Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.21a
msgid "
msgstr Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: paṭiggaṇheyya → paṭigaṇheyya (pts1)
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_749, pts-vp-en.2.324
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.22
msgid “Bhikkhuṃ paneva kulaṃ upagataṃ pūvehi vā manthehi vā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreyya, ākaṅkhamānena bhikkhunā dvattipattapūrā paṭiggahetabbā tato ce uttari paṭiggaṇheyya pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk approaches a family and is invited to take biscuits or cereals, he may accept two or three bowlfuls if he wishes. If he accepts more than that, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.23
msgid Dvattipattapūre paṭiggahetvā tato nīharitvā bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ saṃvibhajitabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he accepts two or three bowlfuls, he should take it away and share it with the monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:1.2.24
msgid Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcī”ti."
msgstr "This is the proper procedure.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.0a
msgid "
msgstr Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, pts-cs-bu-pc34.2.1, ms2V_750
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.1
msgid Bhikkhuṃ paneva kulaṃ upagatanti"
msgstr "A monk approaches a family:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.2
msgid kulaṃ nāma cattāri kulāni—"
msgstr "there are four kinds of families:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.3
msgid khattiyakulaṃ, brāhmaṇakulaṃ, vessakulaṃ, suddakulaṃ."
msgstr "aristocratic families, brahmin families, merchant families, worker families."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_751
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.4
msgid Upagatanti"
msgstr "Approaches:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.5
msgid tattha gataṃ."
msgstr "he has gone there."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_752
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.6
msgid Pūvaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Biscuits:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.7
msgid yaṃ kiñci paheṇakatthāya paṭiyattaṃ."
msgstr "whatever has been prepared for the purpose of sending away."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, ms2V_753
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.8
msgid Manthaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Cereals:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.9
msgid yaṃ kiñci pātheyyatthāya paṭiyattaṃ."
msgstr "whatever has been prepared as provisions for a journey."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_754
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.10
msgid Abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreyyāti"
msgstr "Is invited to take:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.11
msgid yāvatakaṃ icchasi tāvatakaṃ gaṇhāhīti."
msgstr "saying, “Take as much as you like.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, ms2V_755
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.12
msgid Ākaṅkhamānenāti"
msgstr "If he wishes:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.13
msgid icchamānena."
msgstr "if he desires."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc14, ms2V_756
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.14
msgid Dvattipattapūrā paṭiggahetabbāti"
msgstr "He may accept two or three bowlfuls:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.15
msgid dvetayo pattapūrā paṭiggahetabbā."
msgstr "two or three bowlfuls can be accepted."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc15, ms2V_757
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.16
msgid Tato ce uttari paṭigaṇheyyāti"
msgstr "If he accepts more than that:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.17
msgid tatuttari paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he receives more than that, he commit an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc16, ms2V_758
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.18
msgid Dvattipattapūre paṭiggahetvā"
msgstr "If he accepts two or three bowlfuls:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.19
msgid tato nikkhamantena bhikkhuṃ passitvā ācikkhitabbaṃ—"
msgstr "leaving that place and seeing a monk, he should tell him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.20
msgid “amutra mayā dvattipattapūrā paṭiggahitā, mā kho tattha paṭiggaṇhī”ti."
msgstr "“I’ve accepted two or three bowlfuls from such-and-such a place; don’t receive anything from there.”"

#. HTML: <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.21
msgid Sace passitvā na ācikkhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he sees a monk, but does not tell him, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </span><span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.22
msgid Sace ācikkhite paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If one who is told accepts from there regardless, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </span></span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc17, pts-vp-pli4.81, ms2V_759, pts-vp-en.2.325
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.23
msgid Tato nīharitvā bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ saṃvibhajitabbanti"
msgstr "He should take it away and share it with the monks:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.24
msgid paṭikkamanaṃ nīharitvā saṃvibhajitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he should take it away when he is returning from almsround and then share it."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc18, ms2V_760
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.25
msgid Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcīti"
msgstr "This is the proper procedure:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.1.26
msgid ayaṃ tattha anudhammatā."
msgstr "this is the right method."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.2.0a
msgid "
msgstr Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc19, pts-cs-bu-pc34.2.2, ms2V_761
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.2.1
msgid Atirekadvattipattapūre atirekasaññī paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is more than two or three bowlfuls, and he perceives it as more, and he receives it, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.2.2
msgid Atirekadvattipattapūre vematiko paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is more than two or three bowlfuls, but he is unsure if it is, and he receives it, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.2.3
msgid Atirekadvattipattapūre ūnakasaññī paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is more than two or three bowlfuls, but he perceives it as less, and he receives it, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20, ms2V_762
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.2.4
msgid Ūnakadvattipattapūre atirekasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than two or three bowlfuls, but he perceives it as more, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.2.5
msgid Ūnakadvattipattapūre vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than two or three bowlfuls, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.2.6
msgid Ūnakadvattipattapūre ūnakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is less than two or three bowlfuls, and he perceives it as less, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.3.0a
msgid "
msgstr Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc21, pts-cs-bu-pc34.2.3, ms2V_763
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.3.1
msgid Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.3.2
msgid dvattipattapūre paṭiggaṇhāti,"
msgstr "if he accepts two or three bowlfuls;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.3.3
msgid ūnakadvattipattapūre paṭiggaṇhāti,"
msgstr "if he accepts less than two or three bowlfuls;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.3.4
msgid na paheṇakatthāya na pātheyyatthāya paṭiyattaṃ denti,"
msgstr "if they give anything that has not been prepared for sending away or for provisions for a journey;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.3.5
msgid paheṇakatthāya vā pātheyyatthāya vā paṭiyattasesakaṃ denti,"
msgstr "if they give the leftovers from what was prepared for sending away or for provisions for a journey;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.3.6
msgid gamane paṭippassaddhe denti,"
msgstr "if they give after the plans to travel have been canceled;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.3.7
msgid ñātakānaṃ pavāritānaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is from relatives;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.3.8
msgid aññassatthāya,"
msgstr "if it is from those who have given an invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.3.9
msgid attano,"
msgstr "if it is for the benefit of someone else;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.3.10
msgid dhanena,"
msgstr "if it is by means of his own property;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.3.11
msgid ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.3.12
msgid ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc22, ms2V_764
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc34:2.3.13
msgid Kāṇamātusikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr "The fourth rule, the training rule on Kāṇamātā, is finished."


